22// Regular expressions
23// The regular expression holds a single reference to a FixedArray in
24// the kDataOffset field.
25// The FixedArray contains the following data:
26// - tag : type of regexp implementation (not compiled yet, atom or irregexp)
27// - reference to the original source string
28// - reference to the original flag string
29// If it is an atom regexp
30// - a reference to a literal string to search for
31// If it is an irregexp regexp:
32// - a reference to code for Latin1 inputs (bytecode or compiled), or a smi
33// used for tracking the last usage (used for regexp code flushing).
34// - a reference to code for UC16 inputs (bytecode or compiled), or a smi
35// used for tracking the last usage (used for regexp code flushing).
36// - max number of registers used by irregexp implementations.
37// - number of capture registers (output values) of the regexp.
38class JSRegExp : public TorqueGeneratedJSRegExp<JSRegExp, JSObject> {
39 public:
40 enum Type {
41 NOT_COMPILED, // Initial value. No data array has been set yet.
42 ATOM, // A simple string match.
43 IRREGEXP, // Compiled with Irregexp (code or bytecode).
44 EXPERIMENTAL, // Compiled to use the experimental linear time engine.
45 };
46 DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_JS_REG_EXP_FLAGS()

96 static base::Optional<RegExpFlag> FlagFromChar(char c) {
97 base::Optional<RegExpFlag> f = TryRegExpFlagFromChar(c);
98 if (!f.has_value()) return f;
99 if (f.value() == RegExpFlag::kLinear &&
100 !v8_flags.enable_experimental_regexp_engine) {
101 return {};
102 }
103 return f;
104 }

109 static_assert(static_cast<int>(k##Camel) == \
110 static_cast<int>(RegExpFlag::k##Camel));
111 REGEXP_FLAG_LIST(V)

134 static constexpr bool TypeSupportsCaptures(Type t) {
135 return t == IRREGEXP || t == EXPERIMENTAL;
136 }
137
138 // Each capture (including the match itself) needs two registers.
139 static constexpr int RegistersForCaptureCount(int count) {
140 return (count + 1) * 2;
141 }
142 static constexpr int CaptureCountForRegisters(int register_count) {
143 DCHECK_EQ(register_count % 2, 0);
144 DCHECK_GE(register_count, 2);
145 return (register_count - 2) / 2;
146 }
147
148 static constexpr int code_index(bool is_latin1) {
149 return is_latin1 ? kIrregexpLatin1CodeIndex : kIrregexpUC16CodeIndex;
150 }
151
152 static constexpr int bytecode_index(bool is_latin1) {
153 return is_latin1 ? kIrregexpLatin1BytecodeIndex
154 : kIrregexpUC16BytecodeIndex;
155 }

161 /* This is already an in-object field. */
162 // TODO(v8:8944): improve handling of in-object fields
163 static constexpr int kLastIndexOffset = kHeaderSize;
164
165 // The initial value of the last_index field on a new JSRegExp instance.
166 static constexpr int kInitialLastIndexValue = 0;
167
168 // Indices in the data array.
169 static constexpr int kTagIndex = 0;
170 static constexpr int kSourceIndex = kTagIndex + 1;
171 static constexpr int kFlagsIndex = kSourceIndex + 1;
172 static constexpr int kFirstTypeSpecificIndex = kFlagsIndex + 1;
173 static constexpr int kMinDataArrayLength = kFirstTypeSpecificIndex;
174
175 // The data fields are used in different ways depending on the
176 // value of the tag.
177 // Atom regexps (literal strings).
178 static constexpr int kAtomPatternIndex = kFirstTypeSpecificIndex;
179 static constexpr int kAtomDataSize = kAtomPatternIndex + 1;
180
181 // A InstructionStream object or a Smi marker value equal to
182 // kUninitializedValue.
183 static constexpr int kIrregexpLatin1CodeIndex = kFirstTypeSpecificIndex;
184 static constexpr int kIrregexpUC16CodeIndex = kIrregexpLatin1CodeIndex + 1;
185 // A ByteArray object or a Smi marker value equal to kUninitializedValue.
186 static constexpr int kIrregexpLatin1BytecodeIndex =
187 kIrregexpUC16CodeIndex + 1;
188 static constexpr int kIrregexpUC16BytecodeIndex =
189 kIrregexpLatin1BytecodeIndex + 1;
190 // Maximal number of registers used by either Latin1 or UC16.
191 // Only used to check that there is enough stack space
192 static constexpr int kIrregexpMaxRegisterCountIndex =
193 kIrregexpUC16BytecodeIndex + 1;
194 // Number of captures in the compiled regexp.
195 static constexpr int kIrregexpCaptureCountIndex =
196 kIrregexpMaxRegisterCountIndex + 1;
197 // Maps names of named capture groups (at indices 2i) to their corresponding
198 // (1-based) capture group indices (at indices 2i + 1).
199 static constexpr int kIrregexpCaptureNameMapIndex =
200 kIrregexpCaptureCountIndex + 1;
201 // Tier-up ticks are set to the value of the tier-up ticks flag. The value is
202 // decremented on each execution of the bytecode, so that the tier-up
203 // happens once the ticks reach zero.
204 // This value is ignored if the regexp-tier-up flag isn't turned on.
205 static constexpr int kIrregexpTicksUntilTierUpIndex =
206 kIrregexpCaptureNameMapIndex + 1;
207 // A smi containing either the backtracking limit or kNoBacktrackLimit.
208 // TODO(jgruber): If needed, this limit could be packed into other fields
209 // above to save space.
210 static constexpr int kIrregexpBacktrackLimit =
211 kIrregexpTicksUntilTierUpIndex + 1;
212 static constexpr int kIrregexpDataSize = kIrregexpBacktrackLimit + 1;
213
214 // TODO(mbid,v8:10765): At the moment the EXPERIMENTAL data array conforms
215 // to the format of an IRREGEXP data array, with most fields set to some
216 // default/uninitialized value. This is because EXPERIMENTAL and IRREGEXP
217 // regexps take the same code path in `RegExpExecInternal`, which reads off
218 // various fields from the data array. `RegExpExecInternal` should probably
219 // distinguish between EXPERIMENTAL and IRREGEXP, and then we can get rid of
220 // all the IRREGEXP only fields.
221 static constexpr int kExperimentalDataSize = kIrregexpDataSize;
222
223 // In-object fields.
224 static constexpr int kLastIndexFieldIndex = 0;
225 static constexpr int kInObjectFieldCount = 1;
226
227 // The actual object size including in-object fields.
228 static constexpr int Size() {
229 return kHeaderSize + kInObjectFieldCount * kTaggedSize;
230 }
231
232 // Descriptor array index to important methods in the prototype.
233 static constexpr int kExecFunctionDescriptorIndex = 1;
234 static constexpr int kSymbolMatchFunctionDescriptorIndex = 15;
235 static constexpr int kSymbolMatchAllFunctionDescriptorIndex = 16;
236 static constexpr int kSymbolReplaceFunctionDescriptorIndex = 17;
237 static constexpr int kSymbolSearchFunctionDescriptorIndex = 18;
238 static constexpr int kSymbolSplitFunctionDescriptorIndex = 19;
239
240 // The uninitialized value for a regexp code object.
241 static constexpr int kUninitializedValue = -1;
242
243 // If the backtrack limit is set to this marker value, no limit is applied.
244 static constexpr uint32_t kNoBacktrackLimit = 0;
245
246 // The heuristic value for the length of the subject string for which we
247 // tier-up to the compiler immediately, instead of using the interpreter.
248 static constexpr int kTierUpForSubjectLengthValue = 1000;
249
250 // Maximum number of captures allowed.
251 static constexpr int kMaxCaptures = 1 << 16;
252
253 private:

255 inline static const char* FlagsToString(Flags flags, FlagsBuffer* out_buffer);

258 inline void SetDataAt(int index, Tagged<Object> value);

260 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(JSRegExp)
261};

265// JSRegExpResult is just a JSArray with a specific initial map.
266// This initial map adds in-object properties for "index" and "input"
267// properties, as assigned by RegExp.prototype.exec, which allows
268// faster creation of RegExp exec results.
269// This class just holds constants used when creating the result.
270// After creation the result must be treated as a JSArray in all regards.
271class JSRegExpResult
272 : public TorqueGeneratedJSRegExpResult<JSRegExpResult, JSArray> {
273 public:
274 // TODO(joshualitt): We would like to add printers and verifiers to
275 // JSRegExpResult, and maybe JSRegExpResultIndices, but both have the same
276 // instance type as JSArray.
277
278 // Indices of in-object properties.
279 static constexpr int kIndexIndex = 0;
280 static constexpr int kInputIndex = 1;
281 static constexpr int kGroupsIndex = 2;
282
283 // Private internal only fields.
284 static constexpr int kNamesIndex = 3;
285 static constexpr int kRegExpInputIndex = 4;
286 static constexpr int kRegExpLastIndex = 5;
287 static constexpr int kInObjectPropertyCount = 6;
288
289 static constexpr int kMapIndexInContext = Context::REGEXP_RESULT_MAP_INDEX;
290
291 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(JSRegExpResult)
292};
